name: angular
comment:
Angular is a framework for building single page web applications.

Further reading:

  • AngularJS Overview
  • Tutorial
  • Mailing List

forceNewDirectivesAndFilters.name: forceNewDirectivesAndFilters
forceNewDirectivesAndFilters.comment: Creates a child injector that allows loading new directives, filters and services from the provided modules.

ngDirectives.name: ngDirectives
ngDirectives.comment:
Return a List of directive controllers associated with a current Element.

NOTE: This global method is here to make it easier to debug Angular application from the browser's REPL, unit or end-to-end tests. The function is not intended to be called from Angular application.

ngScope.name: ngScope
ngScope.comment:
Return the angular/angular.Scope associated with a current Element.

NOTE: This global method is here to make it easier to debug Angular application from the browser's REPL, unit or end-to-end tests. The function is not intended to be called from Angular application.

ngInjector.name: ngInjector

Return the angular/angular.Injector associated with a current Element.

NOTE: This global method is here to make it easier to debug Angular application from the browser's REPL, unit or end-to-end tests. The function is not intended to be called from Angular application.

ngProbe.comment:
Return the closest angular/angular.ElementProbe object for a given Element.

ngBootstrap.name: ngBootstrap
ngBootstrap.comment:
This method is the main entry point to an angular application.

The angular/angular.ngBootstrap is responsible for:

  1. Locating the root element of the application,
  2. Creating Angular angular/angular.NgZone
  3. Inside the angular/angular.NgZone create an injector
  4. Retrieve the angular/angular.Compiler and compile the root eleement

Parameters:

  • angular/angular.ngBootstrap.module Option application module to add to the angular/angular.Injector.
  • angular/angular.ngBootstrap.modules Optional list of angular/angular.Modules to add to the angular/angular.Injector (if more than one is needed).

  • angular/angular.ngBootstrap.element Optional root element of the application. If non specified, the the root element is looked up using the angular/angular.ngBootstrap.selector. If selector can not identify a root, the root HTML element is used for bootstraping.

  • angular/angular.ngBootstrap.selector Optional CSS selector used to locate the root element for the application.
  • injectorFactor Optional factory responsible for creating the injector.

A typical way to boostrap an Angular application:

Module myAppModule = new Module();
myAppModule.type(MyType);
....
Injector injector = ngBootstrap(module: myAppModule);

class.name: Module
class.preview: A collection of type bindings. Once the module is passed into the injector, the injector creates a copy of the module and all subsequent changes to the module have no effect.

class.name: NgZone
class.preview: A better zone API which implements onTurnDone.

class.name: LongStackTrace
class.preview: Contains the locations of runAsync calls across VM turns.

class.name: Scope
class.preview: angular/angular.Scope is represents a collection of angular/angular.Scope.watches observeers, and angular/angular.Scope.context for the watchers, observers and angular/angular.Scope.evaluations. Scopes structure loosely mimics the DOM structure. Scopes and angular/angular.Views are bound to each other. As scopes are created and destroyed by angular/angular.ViewFactory they are responsible for change detection, change processing and memory management.

class.name: ScopeDigestTTL
class.preview: Allows the configuration of Scope.digest iteration maximum time-to-live value. Digest keeps checking the state of the watcher getters until it can execute one full iteration with no watchers triggering. TTL is used to prevent an infinite loop where watch A triggers watch B which in turn triggers watch A. If the system does not stabilize in TTL iterations then the digest is stopped and an exception is thrown.

class.name: ScopeEvent
class.preview: Injected into the listener function within angular/angular.Scope.on to provide event-specific details to the scope listener.

class.name: Interpolate
class.preview: Compiles a string with markup into an interpolation function. This service is used by the HTML angular/angular.Compiler service for data binding.

class.name: FilterMap
class.preview: Registry of filters at runtime.

class.name: NgFilter
class.preview: Use @angular/angular.NgFilter annotation to register a new filter. A filter is a class with a call method (a callable function).

class.name: ExceptionHandler
class.preview: Any uncaught exception in angular expressions is delegated to this service. The default implementation logs exceptions into console.

class.name: NgDetachAware
class.preview: Implementing directives or components angular/angular.NgDetachAware.detach method will be called when the associated scope is destroyed.

class.name: NgAttachAware
class.preview: Implementing directives or components angular/angular.NgAttachAware.attach method will be called when the next scope digest occurs after component instantiation. It is guaranteed that when angular/angular.NgAttachAware.attach is invoked, that all attribute mappings have already been processed.

class.name: NgCallback
class.preview: When applied as an annotation on a directive field specifies that the field is to be mapped to DOM attribute with the provided angular/angular.AttrFieldAnnotation.attrName. The value of the attribute to be treated as a callback expession, equivalent to & specification.

class.name: NgTwoWay
class.preview: When applied as an annotation on a directive field specifies that the field is to be mapped to DOM attribute with the provided angular/angular.AttrFieldAnnotation.attrName. The value of the attribute to be treated as a two-way expession, equivalent to <=> specification.

class.name: NgOneWayOneTime
class.preview: When applied as an annotation on a directive field specifies that the field is to be mapped to DOM attribute with the provided angular/angular.AttrFieldAnnotation.attrName. The value of the attribute to be treated as a one time one-way expession, equivalent to =>! specification.

class.name: NgOneWay
class.preview: When applied as an annotation on a directive field specifies that the field is to be mapped to DOM attribute with the provided angular/angular.AttrFieldAnnotation.attrName. The value of the attribute to be treated as a one-way expession, equivalent to => specification.

class.name: NgAttr
class.preview: When applied as an annotation on a directive field specifies that the field is to be mapped to DOM attribute with the provided angular/angular.AttrFieldAnnotation.attrName. The value of the attribute to be treated as a string, equivalent to @ specification.

class.name: NgController
class.preview: Meta-data marker placed on a class which should act as a controller for your application.

class.name: NgDirective
class.preview: Meta-data marker placed on a class which should act as a directive.

class.name: NgComponent
class.preview: Meta-data marker placed on a class which should act as a controller for the component. Angular components are a light-weight version of web-components. Angular components use shadow-DOM for rendering their templates.

class.name: LruCache
class.preview: Simple LRU cache.

class.name: UnboundedCache
class.preview: An unbounded cache.

class.name: Cache
class.preview: The Cache interface.

class.name: TemplateCache
class.preview: Infinite cache service for templates loaded from URLs.

class.name: DirectiveSelectorFactory
class.preview: Factory for creating a angular/angular.DirectiveSelector.

class.name: Http
class.preview: The angular/angular.Http service facilitates communication with the remote HTTP servers. It uses dart:html's HttpRequest and provides a number of features on top of the core Dart library.

class.name: HttpDefaults
class.preview: Injected into the angular/angular.Http service. This class contains application-wide HTTP defaults.

class.name: HttpDefaultHeaders
class.preview: Default header configuration.

class.name: HttpResponse
class.preview: The response for an HTTP request. Returned from the angular/angular.Http service.

class.name: HttpResponseConfig
class.preview: The request configuration of the request associated with this response.

class.name: HttpInterceptors
class.preview: A list of angular/angular.HttpInterceptors.

class.name: DefaultTransformDataHttpInterceptor
class.preview: The default transform data interceptor.abstract

class.name: HttpInterceptor
class.preview: HttpInterceptors are used to modify the Http request. They can be added to angular/angular.HttpInterceptors or passed into angular/angular.Http.call.

class.name: HttpBackend
class.preview: HTTP backend used by the angular/angular.Http service that delegates to dart:html's HttpRequest and deals with Dart bugs.

class.name: ElementBinder
class.preview: ElementBinder is created by the Selector and is responsible for instantiating individual directives and binding element properties.

class.name: TemplateLoader
class.preview: TemplateLoader is an asynchronous access to ShadowRoot which is loaded asynchronously. It allows a Component to be notified when its ShadowRoot is ready.

class.name: NodeAttrs
class.preview: NodeAttrs is a facade for element attributes. The facade is responsible for normalizing attribute names as well as allowing access to the value of the directive.

class.name: Cookies
class.preview: Cookies service

class.name: BrowserCookies
class.preview: This class provides low-level acces to the browser's cookies. It is not meant to be used directly by applications. Instead use the Cookies service.

class.name: ElementProbe
class.preview: angular/angular.ElementProbe is attached to each Element in the DOM. Its sole purpose is to allow access to the angular/angular.Injector, angular/angular.Scope, and Directives for debugging and automated test purposes. The information here is not used by Angular in any way.

class.name: ViewCache
class.preview: ViewCache is used to cache the compilation of templates into angular/angular.Views. It can be used synchronously if HTML is known or asynchronously if the template HTML needs to be looked up from the URL.

class.name: WalkingViewFactory
class.preview: ViewFactory is used to create new angular/angular.Views. ViewFactory is created by the angular/angular.Compiler as a result of compiling a template.

class.name: BoundViewFactory
class.preview: BoundViewFactory is a angular/angular.ViewFactory which does not need Injector because it is pre-bound to an injector from the parent. This means that this BoundViewFactory can only be used from within a specific Directive such as NgRepeat, but it can not be stored in a cache.

class.name: ViewPort
class.preview: A ViewPort is an instance of a hole. ViewPorts designate where child angular/angular.Views can be added in parent angular/angular.View. ViewPorts wrap a DOM element, and act as references which allows more views to be added.

class.name: View
class.preview: A View is a fundamental building view of DOM. It is a chunk of DOM which can not be structural changed. It can only have its attributes changed. A View can have angular/angular.ViewPorts embedded in its DOM. A angular/angular.ViewPort can contain other angular/angular.Views and it is the only way in which DOM can be changed structurally.

class.name: ElementWrapper
class.preview: ElementWrapper is an interface for angular/angular.Views and angular/angular.ViewPorts. Its purpose is to allow treating angular/angular.View and angular/angular.ViewPort under same interface so that angular/angular.Views can be added after angular/angular.ViewPort.

class.name: AnimationResult
class.preview: Final result of an animation after it is no longer attached to the element.

class.name: NoOpAnimation
class.preview: Completed animation handle that is used when an animation is ignored and the final effect of the animation is immediatly completed.

class.name: Animation
class.preview: Animation handle for controlling and listening to animation completion.

class.name: NgAnimate
class.preview: The angular/angular.NgAnimate service provides dom lifecycle mangement, detection and analysis of css animations, and hooks for custom animations. When any of these animations are run, angular/angular.Animations are returned so the animation can be controled and so that custom dom manipulations can occur when animations complete.

class.name: NgShadowRootAware
class.preview: Implementing components angular/angular.NgShadowRootAware.onShadowRoot method will be called when the template for the component has been loaded and inserted into Shadow DOM. It is guaranteed that when angular/angular.NgShadowRootAware.onShadowRoot is invoked, that shadow DOM has been loaded and is ready.

class.name: Parser
class.preview: Placeholder for DI. The parser you are looking for is DynamicParser.

class.name: NgModelMaxLengthValidator
class.preview: Validates the model to see if the length of its contents are less than or equal to the maximum length set in place by the HTML maxlength or ng-maxlength attributes present on the input element.

class.name: NgModelMinLengthValidator
class.preview: Validates the model to see if the length of its contents are greater than or equal to the minimum length set in place by the HTML minlength or ng-minlength attributes present on the input element.

class.name: NgModelPatternValidator
class.preview: Validates the model to see if its contents match the given pattern present on either the HTML pattern or ng-pattern attributes present on the input element.

class.name: NgModelNumberValidator
class.preview: Validates the model to see if its contents match a valid number.

class.name: NgModelEmailValidator
class.preview: Validates the model to see if its contents match a valid email pattern.

class.name: NgModelUrlValidator
class.preview: Validates the model to see if its contents match a valid URL pattern.

class.name: NgModelRequiredValidator
class.preview: Validates the model depending if required or ng-required is present on the element.

class.name: NgForm
class.preview: The form directive listens on submission requests and, depending, on if an action is set, the form will automatically either allow or prevent the default browser submission from occurring.

class.name: OptionValueDirective
class.preview: Since the value attribute of the OPTION can only be a string, Angular provides ng-value which allows binding to any expression.

class.name: InputSelectDirective
class.preview: HTML SELECT element with angular data-binding if used with NgModelDirective.

class.name: NgNonBindableDirective
class.preview: Causes the compiler to ignore all Angular directives and markup on descendant nodes of the matching element. Note, however, that other directives and markup on the element are still processed and that only descending the DOM for compilation is prevented.

class.name: NgSwitchDirective
class.preview: The ngSwitch directive is used to conditionally swap DOM structure on your template based on a scope expression. Elements within ngSwitch but without ngSwitchWhen or ngSwitchDefault directives will be preserved at the location as specified in the template.

class.name: NgStyleDirective
class.preview: The ngStyle directive allows you to set CSS style on an HTML element conditionally.

class.name: NgAttributeDirective
class.preview: In SVG some attributes have a specific syntax. Placing {{interpolation}} in those attributes will break the attribute syntax, and browser will clear the attribute.

class.name: NgSourceDirective
class.preview: In browser some attributes have network side-effect. If the attribute has {{interpolation}} in it it may cause browser to fetch bogus URLs.

class.name: NgBooleanAttributeDirective
class.preview: Allows adding and removing the boolean attributes from the element.

class.name: NgShowDirective
class.preview: The ngShow directive shows or hides the given HTML element based on the expression provided to the ngHide attribute. The element is shown or hidden by changing the removing or adding the ng-hide CSS class onto the element.

class.name: NgHideDirective
class.preview: The ngHide directive shows or hides the given HTML element based on the expression provided to the ngHide attribute. The element is shown or hidden by changing the removing or adding the ng-hide CSS class onto the element.

class.name: NgTemplateDirective
class.preview: The NgTemplateElementDirective allows one to preload an Angular template into the angular/angular.TemplateCache. It works on <template> and <script> elements that have type="text/ng-template. For such elements, The entire contents of the elements are loaded into the angular/angular.TemplateCache under the URL specified by the id attribute.

class.name: NgShallowRepeatDirective
class.preview: EXPERIMENTAL: This feature is experimental. We reserve the right to change or delete it.

class.name: NgRepeatDirective
class.preview: The ngRepeat directive instantiates a template once per item from a collection. Each template instance gets its own scope, where the given loop variable is set to the current collection item, and $index is set to the item index or key.

class.name: NgPluralizeDirective
class.preview:
Overview

ngPluralize is a directive that displays messages according to locale rules.

class.preview: Usage:

class.name: NgFalseValue
class.preview: ng-false-value allows you to select any expression to be set to ng-model when checkbox is deselected<input type="checkbox">`.

class.name: NgTrueValue
class.preview: ng-true-value allows you to select any expression to be set to ng-model when checkbox is selected on <input type="checkbox">.

class.name: NgValue
class.preview: Use ng-value directive with <input type="radio"> or <option> to allow binding to values other then strings. This is needed since the value attribute on DOM element <input type="radio" value="foo"> can only be a string. With ng-value one can bind to any object.

class.name: InputNumberLikeDirective
class.preview: Usage:

class.name: InputTextLikeDirective
class.preview: Usage:

class.name: InputCheckboxDirective
class.preview: Usage:

class.name: NgModel
class.preview: Ng-model directive is responsible for reading/writing to the model. The directive itself is headless. (It does not know how to render or what events to listen for.) It is meant to be used with other directives which provide the rendering and listening capabilities. The directive itself knows how to convert the view-value into model-value and vice versa by allowing others to register converters (To be implemented). It also knows how to (in)validate the model and the form in which it is declared (to be implemented)

class.name: NgIncludeDirective
class.preview: Fetches, compiles and includes an external Angular template/HTML.

class.name: NgUnlessDirective
class.preview: The ng-unless directive compliments the ng-if (provided by NgIfAttrDirective) directive.

class.name: NgIfDirective
class.preview: The ng-if directive compliments the ng-unless (provided by NgUnlessAttrDirective) directive.

class.name: NgCloakDirective
class.preview: The ngCloak directive is used to prevent the Angular html template from being briefly displayed by the browser in its raw (uncompiled) form while your application is loading. Use this directive to avoid the undesirable flicker effect caused by the html template display.

class.name: NgEventDirective
class.preview: Allows you to specify custom behavior for DOM UI events such as mouse, keyboard and touch events.

class.name: NgClassEvenDirective
class.preview: The ngClassOdd and ngClassEven directives work exactly as {@link ng.directive:ngClass ngClass}, except it works in conjunction with ngRepeat and takes affect only on odd (even) rows.

class.name: NgClassOddDirective
class.preview: The ngClassOdd and ngClassEven directives work exactly as {@link ng.directive:ngClass ngClass}, except it works in conjunction with ngRepeat and takes affect only on odd (even) rows.

class.name: NgClassDirective
class.preview: The ngClass allows you to set CSS classes on HTML an element, dynamically, by databinding an expression that represents all classes to be added.

class.name: NgBindTemplateDirective
class.preview: The angular/angular.NgBindTemplateDirective specifies that the element text content should be replaced with the interpolation of the template in the ngBindTemplate attribute. Unlike ngBind, the ngBindTemplate can contain multiple {{ }} expressions.

class.name: NgBindHtmlDirective
class.preview: Creates a binding that will innerHTML the result of evaluating the expression bound to ng-bind-html into the current element in a secure way. This expression must evaluate to a string. The innerHTML-ed content will be sanitized using a default NodeValidator constructed as new dom.NodeValidatorBuilder.common(). In a future version, when Strict Contextual Escaping support has been added to Angular.dart, this directive will allow one to bypass the sanitizaton and innerHTML arbitrary trusted HTML.

class.name: NgBindDirective
class.preview: The ngBind attribute tells Angular to replace the text content of the specified HTML element with the value of a given expression, and to update the text content when the value of that expression changes.

class.name: NgADirective
class.preview: @ngdoc directive @name ng.directive:a @restrict E

class.name: UppercaseFilter
class.preview: Converts string to uppercase.

class.name: OrderByFilter
class.preview: Orders the provided angular/dart-core.Iterable by the expression predicate.

class.name: NumberFilter
class.preview: Formats a number as text.

class.name: LowercaseFilter
class.preview: Converts string to lowercase.

class.name: LimitToFilter
class.preview: Creates a new List or String containing only a prefix/suffix of the elements as specified by the limit parameter.

class.name: JsonFilter
class.preview: Allows you to convert a JavaScript object into JSON string. This filter is mostly useful for debugging.

class.name: FilterFilter
class.preview: Selects a subset of items from the provided angular/dart-core.List and returns it as a new angular/dart-core.List.

class.name: DateFilter
class.preview: Formats date to a string based on the requested format. See Dart http://api.dartlang.org/docs/releases/latest/intl/DateFormat.html for full formating options.

class.name: CurrencyFilter
class.preview: Formats a number as a currency (ie $1,234.56). When no currency symbol is provided, '$' used.

class.name: NgBindRouteDirective
class.preview: A directive that allows to bind child components/directives to a specific route.

class.name: RouteProvider
class.preview: Class that can be injected to retrieve information about the current route. For example:

class.name: NgViewDirective
class.preview: A directive that works with the angular/route-client.Router and loads the template associated with the current route.

class.name: NgRoutingHelper
class.preview: A singleton helper service that handles routing initialization, global events and view registries.

class.name: RouteInitializer
class.preview: An interface that must be implemented by the user of routing library and should include the route initialization.

class.name: RouteViewFactory
class.preview: A factory of route to template bindings.

class.name: NgRoutingUsePushState
class.preview: Allows configuration of Router.useFragment. By default angular/angular.NgRoutingUsePushState.usePushState is true, so the router will listen to angular/dart-dom-html.Window.onPopState and route URLs like "http://host:port/foo/bar?baz=qux". Both the path and query parts of the URL are used by the router. If angular/angular.NgRoutingUsePushState.usePushState is false, router will listen to angular/dart-dom-html.Window.onHashChange and route URLs like "http://host:port/path#/foo/bar?baz=qux". Everything after hash (#) is used by the router.

class.name: NgApp
class.preview: Holds a reference to the root of the application used by ngBootstrap.

class.name: AngularModule
class.preview: This is the top level module which describes the whole of angular.

Visibility.name: Visibility
Visibility.comment: Visibility determines if the instance in the defining module is visible to the requesting injector. If true is returned, then the instance from the defining injector is provided. If false is returned, the injector keeps walking up the tree to find another visible instance.

CreationStrategy.name: CreationStrategy
CreationStrategy.comment: Creation strategy is asked to return an instance of the type after [Injector.get] locates the defining injector that has no instance cached. [directInstantation] is true when an instance is created directly from [Injector.instantiate].

DirectiveSelector.name: DirectiveSelector
DirectiveSelector.comment:
DirectiveSelector is a function which given a node it will return a list of [DirectiveRef]s which are triggered by this node.

DirectiveSelector is used by the [Compiler] during the template walking to extract the [DirectiveRef]s.

DirectiveSelector can be created using the [directiveSelectorFactory] method.

The DirectiveSelector supports CSS selectors which do not cross element boundaries only. The selectors can have any mix of element-name, class-names and attribute-names.

Examples:

  element
  .class
  [attribute]
  [attribute=value]
  element[attribute1][attribute2=value]

AttributeChanged.name: AttributeChanged
AttributeChanged.comment: Callback function used to notify of attribute changes.

RouteInitializerFn.name: RouteInitializerFn
RouteInitializerFn.comment:
An typedef that must be implemented by the user of routing library and should include the route initialization.

The function will be called by the framework once the router is instantiated but before [NgBindRouteDirective] and [NgViewDirective].
